e fifteenth an\niiuul svuul Is to he held at Denver\nJanuary, if* to 22, unu it is the best.)\nbailee evur present! d to study pun*\nin lit production, marketing and fa< t\u00ab\nonotfriling thu Krowlng Industry gen\nrally, it will bo u special t uuuto to; j\n..\u2022\u2022t possession of some line slock at i\ni ensuiiublu rules.\nEntries closed December IP) und .1\n11 diiieri'iit Individual filings hud\nI.een lliudo. this lliuludss L'Sllit',\nilogs, sheep uud horses. Two hull-,\nwi. u ami (our curlots of hrceiiing\nutile are cutered lor auction 111 ul\nulllhii there are entries of 1,200 birds\nin the poultry show, and u vast ox-\nonlioti of lurm niuchiuury uml new\nquipnicnt is being Installed. A corn\n*i u ew feature tills year, run\nCulurutfu l\nera! stabilizing and low'er prices to\nconsumers.\nEthelbert Stewart, government\nprb.e expert, believes that 1921 prices\nwill be far more than at present. He\ndeclared that the present business de\npretsion would dis\u00dfappear within u\nfew w'eeks if manufacturers and re\ntailers would give u pthe Idea of\nclinging to war prices.\nSome optimistic factors are: large\nredactions in government receipts j\nfrom luxury taxes, indicating the pub-\nRoumanians Making\nMilitary Preparations\n(Hpeclnl by United IY-mO\nVieitiia, Jan. 3\u2014Military prepara\ntions ur<* being mude by Roumuuiu\nSix new iUdslieviki divisions are on\nthe front King Ferdinand mobilized\nthe classes of 1910, 1911. 1912. 1913.\n1911 and 191 G, und nillltnri/od Rou\nManiun railways.\nThe assignment of former Ruaslun\nterritory to tho allies Is regarded us\n1 u (*os h I til cuuse for military uction\nby the Bolshovlkl.\nLest Navy Ballonists\nFound in Canada\n(Hp.cbil by United Tress.)\nNew York Jun .J The three U S\nnnvy hiiilbonlsts who left Korknwuy\non December l\"tli und wore lost In\nCunada. have been found and are en\nroute to this country, according to a\nmessage from them ut Ontario.\ntho management has had to orect a\njsw ine building costing $2