nt leading the lowers to limit i\nthe construction work now underway\nui<(f sturt no new ships. Harding,\nhowever, lias declared for a navy\nlarge enough to protect our merchant\nmarine and defend American shores\nBank Robber Killed\nand Loot Recovered\n(Hpciul by United Press.)\nSpringfield. Tenn., Dec. 31 -After\n|u lone huudit had held up the Peo\npli a bank here today, securing SSO.\n000 in Liberty bonds, the hundit was J\ni killed In a duel with the sheriff and\ntho bonds recovered.\nWilson\u2019s Peace Trip\nProves Costly Item\nA special message giving the com\nplote expenses of th American Peace\nCoin mission during its w ork abroad\nwas transmitted to the senate recent\nIv liy President Wilson.\nTotal expenditures amounted to 1\n$1,651.19109 from December. 191*1. to 1\nDecember 4. 1920. The amount uelitul 1\nl lv paid out wus $1,703,712 06. but r 1\npayments and gains In exchange ro\nil need this by $52,520.97.\nSome of tin* larger items were:\nTravel and subsistence $29,442; 1\nsubsistence $193,629; salaries 9200.-\nl 71; wages and employees at Hotel, 1\nCHllon, $131,507, rents, $176,853;!'\n1 food, hotel and kitchen supplies, $293.- 1\n1 560; hire ond laundering of llncu at\nhot.fl, {64.9(3; damiiKi. nml torn, or\nproperty ut hotol, $125,870.\nYurlous missions to Russia. Ger\nmany. Posen, Turkey. Holland uud Ar- 1\nmen la cost f.'\u2019\u2022ty,?2G. Purchase of utt\ntutnohlloii amounted to $14,602. und 1\nconfidential expenses or Presidential 1\narty $17,534.\nt'ol. K M llouao mill Henry White, 1\ntin* statement showed. received\nI monthly sulurics of sl.ooo un commis\nsioners. While Robert Lansing, for- 1\nmer secretary of state, und General\nTusker 11. lillss, other commissioners.\nhud their actual expenses paid\nThe accounts showed refunds by\nPresident Wilson of 914.70 francs for\nexpenses while at Home; by Col 1\nHouse of 10,042 francs for official en-\ntertslnment from December 1. 1918. J\nto June 3, 1919; Secretary Lansing 1\nof 1.589 francs for tip