officially denied It had at\ntempted to use tho big stick In ob-\nI tabling favorable reparation dec!-\nsions. Germany denies threatening\nth*\u00bb breaking off of UVe Brussels rort\njfe-once If made to disarm the clti-\nI zeds guard.\nTJie situation is complicated by do\nmauds of Russian goal miners that\nI tho Rnvarlun guard lx disarmed, be\ncause Its retention amongst them\nmight cause a French invasion of\nI that district.\nSeek Scalp of Mayor\nThompson of Chicago\nChicago, Dt\u2018( 29. (United Press.)\nThough Mayor William Hale\nThompson's term does not expire for\nmore than two years, democrats claim\nthey have discovered u flaw in the\nlaw whereby a four year mayorallty\nterm wus authorized which would end\nThompson\u2019s term next spring uud\nforce a new election.\nAs a result of the discovery the\n1 democrats art Considering u plat,\nwhereby they would Institute court\nproceedings In an effort to fore- the\nChicago Board of Elections to call a\nn.uyorajity election.\nDemocrats s\u00ab in this u hope of\nlauding the pr for themselves, be\ncause of a split ln yepuhllt an ranks.\nThey have already started groom\nIn- candidates and then- Is t tmng\nmovement to stair. 1 a back for\nCarter H Harrison, several times\nmayor of Chicago.\nShould tho democrats successful\ni In upsetting the Jr.w on terms of may\nors It would moan that mayorallty\nelections would huvr to be held in a\nnumber of Illinois cities.\n\nNAVAL BOARD FIGHTS\nBILL FOR DISARMAMENT\nINTRODUCED BY BORAH\n1 Washington, Jan. 3~l)isarmu-\nmeut supporters are bucking 1\nBomb\u2019s resolution railing for en\nJ agreement between the bulled J\nStates. Groat Britain and Jupati\nto limit naval strength. They\ndudnre this will avoid war men-\n11 ace and save lilllloiim of dollars.\nIt Is believed the senate will\npsss it. i\nThn naval hnaj-d will oppose J\ni Un bill, declaring thn develop 11\nment of a merchant marine\ncalls for u navy saoood to nono, J\n1 (hrt the position occupied hy 1\nthe United Sla